      "message": "[Critical] Line 157: shutdownComplete_ is set to true before the dispatched cleanup runs, so the wait predicate below can return immediately. If asio::dispatch queues the lambda, terminate() can return while the lambda still captures the stack-local cv by reference, creating a use-after-scope and skipping cleanup. Use a separate shutdown-requested flag for unblocking readResponse(), or wait on a separate local completion flag that is only set by terminate(cv) after cleanup.",
