      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 211: The socket validity check uses natpmpHdl_.s as a boolean. That treats fd 0 as invalid and negative/INVALID_SOCKET values as valid on some platforms, which can skip closing a real socket or call closenatpmp() on an invalid handle. Use the platform\u0027s invalid-socket sentinel explicitly, e.g. compare against -1 on POSIX and INVALID_SOCKET on Windows, preferably via a small helper.",
      "revId": "8b2f014d27ad9849e69c9a9d36c72c88fd3272ce",
