      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 384: readResponse() reads shutdownComplete_ without holding natpmpMutex_, while terminate() writes it under the mutex from another thread. This is a data race and undefined behavior. Make the shutdown-request state atomic, or read it under the same mutex. Prefer a separate std::atomic_bool shutdownRequested_ so this polling path does not need to block.",
